research_municipality_step.notes: Plano, TX operates under a Council-Manager form of government. The City Council consists of the Mayor and seven City Council members, all elected at-large. Place 6 is always the Mayor. Places 1-4 have residency requirements. The 'mayor_council' government type was chosen as the closest fit from the provided options, given the elected mayor and council structure. There was a slight conflict in one source regarding Maria Tu and Julie Holmer both being listed as 'Deputy Mayor Pro Tem, Place 1'; however, other sources consistently list Maria Tu as Mayor Pro Tem and Julie Holmer as Deputy Mayor Pro Tem. Place 7 for Julie Holmer was determined by elimination, as all other places were accounted for among the 8 council positions.
